<br>11. A journal bearing 75MM long supports a load of 7.3KN on a 50mm diameter journal turning at 750RPM. The dimeteral clearance is 0.07mm. What should be the viscosity of oil if the operating temperature of the bearing surface is to be limited to 75degree centigrade when in still air at 20 <sup>o</sup>C. 
<br>
<br>12. A 100 diameter shaft operating at 2000RPM is supported by means of a 150mm long full journal bearing which is subjected to a radial load of 43KN . Operating temperature of the oil is limited to 80<sup>o</sup>C and the surrounding air temp. Is 38<sup>o</sup>C. Assume P=30*10<sup>-6</sup> determine the coefficient of friction, bearing pressure, heat generated, heat dissipated, oil use. Is artificial cooling is required. 
